                    <text x="210" y="40" font-family="Inter" font-style="italic" font-size="9" fill="#64748B">"Never louder than lovely"</text>
                </svg>
                <div class="illustrate-label">Fig 1.1: Striking the silver center. Note the flush, unindented arrangement of black and white bars.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="action">Invite child to strike bars along the pattern.</div>
            <div class="dialogue">"Want to try the steps with your mallet? Follow the pattern."</div>

            <div class="action">Step back, observe. Silent watch, nod encouragement. Compare to staff notation card.</div>
            <div class="dialogue">"This is how it looks on paper—same pattern, just written."</div>

            <h2 class="font-sans font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-amber-600 mt-16 mb-8 border-b pb-2 italic">Presentation II: Constructing a New Scale</h2>

            <div class="action">Move the strip to begin on a different pitch bar. Pull out the corresponding keys with two fingers.</div>
            <div class="dialogue">"Let’s begin here instead. Does it still sound like a scale?"</div>

            <div class="action">Play full sequence slowly, tapping the silver center, pause at end.</div>
            <div class="dialogue">"Major scale—new home note. Listen to the feeling."</div>

            <div class="illustrate">
                <svg width="450" height="200" viewBox="0 0 450 200" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                    <!-- Base Board -->
